post_text:
NEW STAFF AT SES FOR 2020-2021
Salisbury Elementary welcomed students Monday with four new staff members. Katelyn Howard is the new secretary in the office. She is a Salisbury R-IV graduate who looks forward to serving her community in her new role. Another Salisbury R-IV alumni, Gretchen Atkinson, is serving the students of SES this year as a paraprofessional. Abby Roach is starting her teaching career at SES in third grade and Hannah Selsor has returned to mid-Missouri to teach 4-6 Math. Both are graduates of Central Methodist University. All four bring great experiences and knowledge to the excellent team at SES.
text:
NEW STAFF AT SES FOR 2020-2021
Salisbury Elementary welcomed students Monday with four new staff members. Katelyn Howard is the new secretary in the office. She is a Salisbury R-IV graduate who looks forward to serving her community in her new role. Another Salisbury R-IV alumni, Gretchen Atkinson, is serving the students of SES this year as a paraprofessional. Abby Roach is starting her teaching career at SES in third grade and Hannah Selsor has returned to mid-Missouri to teach 4-6 Math. Both are graduates of Central Methodist University. All four bring great experiences and knowledge to the excellent team at SES.

post_text:
SHS Student Council Helps Special Olympics Missouri
Student Council members participated in an event to help the Special Olympic Athletes of Northern Missouri. Since the Special Olympics were cancelled due to Covid-19 student councils were asked to participate in a virtual parade to show their support for the athletes. Students were tasked with decorating their cars with signs and holding a mini parade. Members present included: Bottom row (left to right) Brooke Stefankiewicz, Vice President, Kaylyn Hinkle, Secretary, Stran Henry, President. Top row (left to right) Connor Fawks, Senior Class Rep., Karen See, Katie See, Junior Class Reps.,Colten Henry, Freshman Class Rep., Sydney Stundebeck, Reporter, and Mylie Brown, Junior Class Rep. Thanks to everyone who participated and especially MASC for giving us this opportunity!

post_text: Parents As Teachers Coordinator/Paraprofessional - The Salisbury R-IV School District is currently accepting applications for a part-time PAT coordinator/ part-time paraprofessional. The two responsibilities together would equal full-time hourly pay with benefits included. Qualifications for this position include the following: Must have a substitute certificate and successful completion of a background check. PAT training will be provided by the district. This position will remain open until a suitable candidate has been hired. Please send the completed application (link provided below), letter of interest, resume and a copy of your Substitute Certificate to Salisbury R-IV School District, 1000 S. Maple Ave., Salisbury, MO 65281, Attn: Mrs. Robin Gebhardt

post_text:
Salisbury R-IV School District will be re-scheduling prom, senior awards, baccalaureate and graduation for the weekend of July 17-19. 2020 Salisbury HS Graduation/Prom weekend events will be as follows: Friday, July 17th-Prom, Saturday, July 18th-Senior Awards/Baccalaureate and Sunday, July 19th-Graduation. Specific times and more information for each activity will be announced at a later date. Building administrators will be sending out parent letters by email later today with specific details and plans for wrapping up this school year. The last day of district provided lunches will be Friday, May 22. Thank you for your patience and understanding as we have worked to meet the needs of all students.

Sincerely,

Troy Clawson, Superintendent
Salisbury R-IV School District.

post_text: In show of support for the 2020 Senior Class, the Salisbury R-IV Schools will be joining schools around the country and state by turning on our football field lights on Friday, April 10th, at 8:20 pm, which is 20:20 military time, and leaving them lit for 20 minutes and 20 seconds to honor the class of 2020. The Salisbury Parks and Recreation Board will also join in this support by turning on the baseball field lights during this time.

post_text:
The Salisbury R-IV School District school closure is being extended through Friday, April 24, 2020. The Chariton County Commission, in conjunction with the Health Department has issued a Stay at Home Order effective Monday, March 30th, 2020 until Friday, April 24, 2020. The school district will continue to offer free meals to all students 18 and under. Meals are available from 11:15-12:15 Monday-Friday by Grab and Go at Salisbury Elementary School or by delivery. If you are not currently receiving meals, but would like to, a link can be found on the Salisbury R-IV Website. I encourage everyone to stay safe and healthy during these difficult times. Thank you for you continued support.

Troy Clawson
Superintendent
Salisbury R-IV School District

post_text: Salisbury R-IV School District will be providing free meals to students 18 & under in our school district beginning Monday, March 23rd. This is available to all Salisbury R-IV and St. Joseph Catholic students. Our plan is to make the meals available Monday-Friday. Each meal will include a lunch as well as breakfast item for the next day. Lunches are available for grab and go from 11:15 to 12:15 at Salisbury Elementary School (Lane on North side of the building). If you are unable to do pick-up, meals can be delivered to your home. We ask all people interested in meals to click the Salisbury R-IV Free Meals link and fill out the form. We are prepared to offer meals throughout the school closure. If you need to change your selection on whether or not you want meals or you need to change your delivery/pick up option, please email our Food Services Director Mrs. Brooke Sellers: bsellers@salisbury.k12.mo.us Thank you for your continued support.

post_text: Salisbury R-IV School District, in response to the COVID-19 pandemic, will close school following Spring Break on Monday, March 23rd thru Friday, April 3rd. Beginning Wed. March 18th, all school activities, including athletic and extra-curricular practices and competitions, will be canceled during the time school is closed. We are planning to return to our regular schedule on Monday, April 6th. We will continue to seek guidance from the county and state health departments in the event the closure should extend past April 6th. The deep cleaning and sanitation process in all district buildings will continue during the closure. Please follow the advice of our health officials. Practice proper hand washing and social distancing. Thank you for your continued support.

Due to predicted inclement weather on Wednesday the officer team and advisors have decided to move our annual FFA Supporters’ Breakfast to Thursday. Same time and location. This will also allow our community members to enjoy our famous bacon and sausage after Lent.

Please help us spread the word. We appreciate your support and look forward to seeing everyone Thursday at the High School Lobby at 6:30 am until 8:00 am.
